          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Pell Grant Modernization Act </b></p> <p>This bill amends the Higher Education Act of 1965 to modify eligibility requirements under the Federal Pell Grant Program. Specifically, the bill reduces the numbers of semesters a student is eligible to receive Pell Grants from 12 semesters to 10 semesters. </p> <p>In addition, the bill increases the number of credits students must take each semester in order to be considered a full-time student.</p>]]></text>
